gomodel:SYNGO_555  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Localization of Munc13 isoforms at the calyx of Held synapse.\n- Fig.1 shows localization of native protein with subtype-specific antibodies. Strong colocalization with the presynaptic marker VGlut1 together with a lack of staining of the postsynaptic MNTB cell body strongly support a presynaptic localization.\n- Fig.2/3 shows localization of genetically encoded EGFP attached to native mouse Munc13 paralogs. Strong colocalization with the presynaptic markers VGlut1 and Bassoon together with a lack of staining of the postsynaptic MNTB cell body strongly support a presynaptic localization.\nTable 1 presents a quantification of Munc13-1 staining intensity at Bassoon-immunoreactive active zones, demonstrating a high degree of localization to the presynaptic active zone.. Experimental description: Figure 1 shows expression of Munc13-1 in mouse calyx of Held synapses. As a negative control for the antibody staining calyces from Munc13-1 KO mice were used. The mice have been described previously (Augustin et al., 2001; Varoqueaux et al., 2002).\nFig.2 and Fig.3 show localization of genetically encoded EGFP attached to native mouse Munc13 paralogs. Munc13-XFP mice have been described previously (Kalla et al., 2006; Cooper et al., 2012)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" ;
        dc:date           "2017-05-17" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_555" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

